programme.title: Submission Possible
programme.desc: S1 E2 | In Episode Two, Young visits the wet and wild city of Seattle - the Emerald City that sits amongst the rainforests of the Pacific Northwest. Bring your galoshes and go puddle splashing with Young as they spelunk into kink as a movement in Seattle from feminist burlesque, embodied spanking practices, tassle twirling, the importance of representation on the stage and in porn, and even service centric kinky tea parties. Madison’s explorations lead them to, NEVE; a performer, dancer and queer porn performer, Indigo Blue; burlesque icon and founder of the Academy of Burlesque, Mx Pucks A Plenty; the non-binary femme-daddy your mama didn’t warn you about, and professional disciplinarian; Miss Jenn Davis.

programme.title: Margaret Cho: Psycho
programme.desc: Comedian Margaret Cho performs in front of a live audience in this provocative and hilarious comedy special event, tackling off-limits issues from Boko Haram to female empowerment with her razor sharp insight and wit.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: For My Wife
programme.desc: A feature documentary chronicling the making of an activist. After the tragic death of her wife, Charlene Strong was thrust into the spotlight becoming a powerful voice ;for the equal rights of same-sex couples and their families.

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.title: Queens of Kings
programme.desc: S2 E1-7↵↵Thorgy Thor is one of the veteran queens of the Brooklyn drag scene. In addition to being a top 6 finalist in RuPaul's Drag Race Season 8, Thorgy Thor has captured the hearts and respect of her peers and fans alike. Behind the makeup, Thorgy is a trained cellist, and in this episode, in addition to giving her perspective on the scene she has long called home, Thorgy expresses her long held desire to merge her love of drag and classical music.↵↵Amber may not look like your typical drag queen when painted up, but her performance and charisma speak for themselves. Amber's engaging performance and her descriptions of gender fluidity and how it has affected her life provide for not only an entertaining but inspiring and informational experience.↵↵Biblegirl represents a new type of drag queen for a new generation. In addition to her stunning performances, Biblegirl is known as a "social media queen" and has garnered a reputation of being rough around the edges, especially when dealing with her online haters. In this episode, Biblegirl explores her embrace of the online community and how she thinks it has expanded the way drag performers can interact with their fans and build it into a brand.↵↵Aja has burst onto the Brooklyn drag scene and left her mark. Originally from Bushwick before it was hip, Aja has, throughout her career, bridged the gap between the outer boroughs and introduced a new sense of vitality to a vibrant scene. Through her unique looks and her much-applauded styling and sewing skills, Aja has earned the respect of her peers and uses such praise to inspire her audience.↵↵Patti Spliff is a stunning art drag queen who has captivated the Brooklyn scene. Follow Patti as she leaves her Brooklyn surroundings to perform in Fire Island Pines, a common summer stomping ground for the New York gay community. While the queens may be out of the city, the high heels remain on the beach.↵↵Charlene, also featured in season 1 of Queens of Kings, has changed since her last appearance. Since Season 1, Charlene has begun the medical process of transitioning from male to female. This episode examines the progress of Charlene's transitions and also explores the effect these changes have made on her mental health and view of the world and her fellow performers.↵↵Bushwig is Brooklyn's largest drag festival, and was created by veteran drag performer Horrorchata. Focusing on Bushwig 2015, the festival featured performances from the cast of Queens of Kings as well as Lady Bunny, Horrorchata, and other Brooklyn drag legends.

programme.title: Submission Possible
programme.desc: S1 E3 | In Episode Three, Young explores the quirky and kinky city of Portland, Oregon, a city full of people who stand up for what they believe in. Portland isn’t afraid to remind us all that kink is political AF! From Strippers fighting for equal rights and pay amidst a pandemic to Foodie Activism for Sex Workers, Young connects with fellow sexual revolutionaries making a difference in their city. Madison’s explorations lead them to an amazing cast of characters including Nikeisah C. Newton, a chef turned sex worker activist, Cat Hollis - a stripper rights activist and organizer for the Portland Stripper’s Strike, Arabelle Raphael - sex worker and fetishist, and the donut daddy of our dreams, Dadi Iris, who shows us just what those donut holes are really for!

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! programme.title: Cancerpants
programme.desc: A community rallies around a woman battling breast cancer in this warm and insightful story of triumph that will arm women with cancer worldwide.

programme.title: Desert Migration
programme.desc: Saved by the introduction of protease inhibitors in the mid-1990s, many HIV positive men needed to rebuild the lives they thought they'd never be able to live. In an effort to make peace with the virus inside them, some migrated to California's Palm Springs in the hope of finding a healing desert oasis. But is this environment, with its tolerant population and constant sunshine, enough to heal their shattered bodies and dispel their lingering grief?

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: The Queen Of Ireland
programme.desc: How one man in a dress is changing the world. The Queen of Ireland is a documentary that follows drag queen Panti Bliss: part glamorous aunt, part Jessica Rabbit, she's a wittily incisive performer with charisma to burn who is widely regarded as one of the best drag queens in the world. Created by Rory O’Neill, Panti is also an accidental activist and in her own words ‘a court jester, whose role is to say the un-sayable’. In recent years, Rory has become a figurehead for LGBT rights in Ireland and since the 2014 scandal around Pantigate, his fight for equality and against homophobia has become recognised across the world. The Queen of Ireland follows drag queen Panti Bliss. Created by Rory O’Neill, In recent years, Rory and Panti have become a figurehead for LGBT rights in Ireland and since the 2014 scandal around Pantigate, his fight for equality and against homophobia has become recognised across the world.

programme.title: Victor's Last Class
programme.desc: A brazen acting teacher suffering from chronic pain announces he is going to end his life, and spends the next five months hashing the decision out with the young filmmaker who attempts to change his mind.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Equality U
programme.desc: Equality U is a feature-length documentary following 34 young activists on the Soulforce Equality Ride. At some stops they're welcomed with open arms, at others they're arrested for trespassing or for simply attempting to open up a dialog. At every stop, they're connecting with young people who've often never met an openly gay, lesbian, bisexual or transgender person who is comfortable with who they are.

L'ultimo tempo di questa sinfonia, composta nel 1823, è un vero successo della musica classica. programme.title: Verbier Festival: Boris Berezovsky
programme.desc: Boris Berezovsky è considerato uno dei migliori rappresentanti della scuola pianistica russa, soprattutto per la sua potente tecnica. Per il 15° anniversario del Verbier Festival, in programma un recital con la Sonata in si minore di Franz Liszt, seguito da brani di Schumann. Un vero e proprio viaggio nel romanticismo.

programme.title: Esa-Pekka Salonen - Joyce DiDonato
programme.desc: Dal 1994, il Festival di Verbier è un luogo d'incontro musicale internazionale nella Svizzera francese. Grandi artisti vi si esibiscono ogni anno davanti a un pubblico fedele. Nel 2015, il Festival accoglie il brillante mezzosoprano americano Joyce DiDonato. Eseguirà Summer Nights, Op. 7 di Hector Berlioz, sotto la direzione di Esa-Pekka Solonen, il famoso direttore d'orchestra finlandese. Si tratta di sei melodie francesi su bellissime poesie di Théophile Gautier da La Comédie de la mort.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. Riunisce tutti i giovani musicisti israeliani e dei paesi arabi vicini - come ad esempio la Siria, la Giordania o i territori palestinesi - con un unico obiettivo: gettare dei ponti fra le comunità attraverso la musica. In diretta dalla Philharmonie di Berlino nel 2006, interpretano l’imponente nona sinfonia di Beethoven.

programme.title: J.S. Bach: Organ Concerts
programme.desc: Per rendere omaggio a Johann Sebastian Bach che ha servito per 27 anni come "maestro di cappella" nella chiesa di San Tommaso a Lipsia, l'organista Ullrich Böhme dà un concerto sul nuovo organo della chiesa: una replica del modello storico che suonava Bach.

programme.title: Jakub Jozef Orlinski- Il Pomo D'Oro
programme.desc: Il controtenore polacco Jakub Józef Orlinski si è guadagnato in breve tempo la reputazione di cantante dalla sorprendente padronanza vocale e dall'audacia scenica. Questo concerto riflette la tanto attesa uscita del suo primo album, Anima Sacra, un recital di arie sacre del XVIII secolo recentemente riscoperte con il gruppo barocco Il Pomo d'oro.

programme.title: Danza Contemporánea de Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba non è solo famosa per i suoi sigari, ma anche per la sua vita culturale molto ricca - dove la danza gioca un ruolo importante. Nel film di Patrick Lauze, la compagnia Danza - Contemporánea de Cuba, creata nel 1959, esegue tre danze sacre al Teatro Nazionale Alicia Alonso all'Avana, Cuba.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker - S. Rattle

programme.title: Paolo Arrivabeni - ORW
programme.desc: L'opera è sinonimo di cantanti. Eppure l'orchestra sinfonica gioca un ruolo cruciale in queste opere musicali e teatrali. L'Orchestre Royal de Wallonie - Liège, sotto la direzione di Paolo Arrivabeni, ci introduce quindi alla ricchezza della musica strumentale di alcune opere.

programme.title: Giuseppe Verdi: La Traviata - ORW
programme.desc: La Traviata, "La Devota", un'opera in tre atti, con un libretto di Francesco Maria Piave basato sul romanzo e la commedia La Dame aux Camélias di Alexandre Dumas fils, è una delle opere più popolari. Rappresenta la redenzione attraverso l'amore per mezzo del personaggio di Violetta. Questo ruolo, notevolmente interpretato da Patrizia Ciofi che unisce forza e fragilità, richiede assoluto virtuosismo.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. programme.title: Giuseppe Verdi: Nabucco
programme.desc: Nel 586 a.C., Nabucco, re di Babilonia, tenne gli ebrei prigionieri in Babilonia. Questa è l'origine del famoso coro Va, pensiero, o Coro degli schiavi, un poema lirico che è considerato un inno alla libertà. L'orchestra e il coro dell'Opera di Zurigo sotto la direzione di Fabio Luisi eseguono con brio questa famosa opera di Giuseppe Verdi.

programme.title: Beethoven - Daniel Barenboim
programme.desc: Qui l'illustre direttore d'orchestra Daniel Barenboim suona e dirige i cinque concerti di Beethoven con l'Orchestra della Staatskapelle di Berlino in occasione del suo 65° compleanno. Il Concerto n. 5 in MI bemolle maggiore, noto come "L'Imperatore", vede il maestro rivoluzionare la forma con un primo movimento lungo seicento battute. Un'improvvisazione messa per iscritto?

programme.title: Ivan Fischer: Schubert and Bruckner
programme.desc: Sotto la direzione magistrale di Iván Fischer, l'orchestra esegue due opere incompiute del periodo romantico. Questo intenso programma, eseguito con sentimento e profondità dalla Budapest Festival Orchestra, ci immerge immediatamente in un abisso emotivo.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: Balanchine: Jewels - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Girato al Teatro Mariinsky, questo spettacolo vede la partecipazione di alcuni dei più famosi ballerini del teatro di San Pietroburgo, tra cui Ulyana Lopatkina, Igor Zelensky e Andrian Fadeyev, accanto al direttore d'orchestra Tugan Sokhiev. I Gioielli di George Balanchine sono parte integrante del repertorio della compagnia - uno dei più grandi al mondo, sia per numero che per fama.

Non è stato certo un caso che abbia suonato Wanderer Fantasy di Schubert, la prima opera che il suo insegnante del Curtis Institute, Gary Graffman, aveva registrato e usato per concludere il concerto delle Réminiscences Du Don Juan de Mozart di Liszt, associato ai più grandi virtuosi del pianoforte.

Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Verbier Festival: Evgeny Kissin
programme.desc: Autentica star del pianoforte, il musicista russo Evgeny Kissin è ospite fisso del Verbier Festival in Svizzera, dove si è esibito più volte dalla prima edizione del 1994. La Sonata per pianoforte n. 59 di Haydn, la Sonata per pianoforte n. 32 di Beethoven e la "Melodia" di Christoph Willibald Gluck da Orfeo ed Euridice offrono a Kissin l'opportunità di mostrare la portata del suo virtuosismo e il lirismo delle sue interpretazioni, ma anche il suo carisma fenomenale.
